Majority of ADC's take {{summoner:4}} {{summoner:7}} 

There is no such thing as boot enchantments anymore.

First item on Jinx should usually be an {{item:3031}}. Although you can go {{item:3072}}  or even just {{item:1038}}  then go into your attack speed item. Usually {{item:3085}} but {{item:3046}}  is also good.

My Jinx full build is usually something like: {{item:3031}} {{item:3085}} {{item:3046}} {{item:3139}} {{item:3006}} {{item:3072}}

Firecracker Jinx is her best skin but the Slayer Jinx is cool too (though you can only buy it on Halloween).

Ok, I'm a Jinx main and I'm happy to help. 

I take {{summoner:4}}  and {{summoner:7}} 
My first item is an {{item:3031}} followed by {{item:3085}} and then get {{item:3006}} 
Then I will generally go for a {{item:3094}} into {{item:3072}} or the other way around, it really depends.
My final item is a range of different things, here's a few: {{item:3139}} {{item:3036}} {{item:3046}} 
Hope this helps! Add me if you'd like, I'd be happy to play a couple of games with you and show you how to utilise these builds if you'd like?
